{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Phase 2b: Feature Engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we will take our cleaned text and create the feature matrices that our machine learning models need. We will prepare:\n",
    "1. **TF-IDF Features**: Used for Naive Bayes and Logistic Regression.\n",
    "2. **Padded Sequences**: Used for the LSTM Deep Learning model (embedding layer will act as Word2Vec).\n",
    "\n",
    "We will also split our data into Train, Validation, and Test sets."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import scipy.sparse\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add the parent directory to sys.path so we can import from src\n",
    "sys.path.append(os.path.abspath('..'))\n",
    "from src.feature_extraction import FeatureExtractor"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load Cleaned Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv('../data/cleaned_reviews.csv')\n",
    "df = df.dropna(subset=['cleaned_text'])\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(df)} cleaned reviews.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "X = df['cleaned_text'].values\n",
    "y = df['sentiment'].values"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Train / Validation / Test Split\n",
    "We split the data: 70% Train, 15% Validation, 15% Test."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_temp, X_test, y_temp, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.15, random_state=42, stratify=y)\n",
    "X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(X_temp, y_temp, test_size=0.1765, random_state=42, stratify=y_temp)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Train size: {len(X_train)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Validation size: {len(X_val)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Test size: {len(X_test)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Extract Features\n",
    "We'll use our `FeatureExtractor` to generate TF-IDF matrices (max 5,000 features) and Sequences (max length 100)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "extractor = FeatureExtractor(max_features=5000, max_sequence_length=100)\n",
    "\n",
    "# -- TF-IDF --\n",
    "print(\"Generating TF-IDF features...\")\n",
    "X_train_tfidf = extractor.fit_tfidf(X_train)\n",
    "X_val_tfidf = extractor.transform_tfidf(X_val)\n",
    "X_test_tfidf = extractor.transform_tfidf(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "# -- Sequences (for Word2Vec / LSTM) --\n",
    "print(\"Generating token sequences...\")\n",
    "X_train_seq = extractor.fit_word2vec_sequences(X_train)\n",
    "X_val_seq = extractor.transform_word2vec_sequences(X_val)\n",
    "X_test_seq = extractor.transform_word2vec_sequences(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"TF-IDF shape (Train): {X_train_tfidf.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Sequence shape (Train): {X_train_seq.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Save Extractor Models and Data\n",
    "We need to save the fitted vectorizers so we can use them during inference in production. We will also save the processed feature matrices to disk so Phase 3 (Model Training) can just load them."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "extractor.save_extractors('../models')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save Labels\n",
    "np.save('../data/y_train.npy', y_train)\n",
    "np.save('../data/y_val.npy', y_val)\n",
    "np.save('../data/y_test.npy', y_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save Sequences\n",
    "np.save('../data/X_train_seq.npy', X_train_seq)\n",
    "np.save('../data/X_val_seq.npy', X_val_seq)\n",
    "np.save('../data/X_test_seq.npy', X_test_seq)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save TF-IDF (sparse matrices)\n",
    "scipy.sparse.save_npz('../data/X_train_tfidf.npz', X_train_tfidf)\n",
    "scipy.sparse.save_npz('../data/X_val_tfidf.npz', X_val_tfidf)\n",
    "scipy.sparse.save_npz('../data/X_test_tfidf.npz', X_test_tfidf)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"All features and labels saved successfully in the 'data' folder.\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
